    • Method Detail

      • hasCustomLoader

        default boolean hasCustomLoader(IResourceManager manager,
                                ResourceLocation location)
        The result of this function determines is the below 'load' function is called, and the default vanilla loading code is bypassed completely.
        Parameters:
        manager - Main resource manager
        location - File resource location
        Returns:
        True to use your own custom load code and bypass vanilla loading.

      • load

        default boolean load(IResourceManager manager,
                     ResourceLocation location,
                     java.util.function.Function<ResourceLocation,TextureAtlasSprite> textureGetter)
        Load the specified resource as this sprite's data. Returning false from this function will prevent this icon from being stitched onto the master texture.
        Parameters:
        manager - Main resource manager
        location - File resource location
        textureGetter - accessor for dependencies. All of them will be loaded before this one
        Returns:
        False to prevent this Icon from being stitched

      • getDependencies

        default java.util.Collection<ResourceLocation> getDependencies()
        Returns:
        all textures that should be loaded before this texture.
